{
  "doc_id": "58462",
  "text": "Ideally, we want mean latency to be on target. Higher latencies indicate bad interactive response, while lower latencies indicate an unnecessary sacrifice of fidelity. We also want the coefficient of variation to be small: variability in performance leads to a bad user experience [CITATION_1] . High variation also indicates that the system is often off-target: in other words, not implementing the adaptive policy well.",
